lyrics:
[verse]
There's a snail in the holler, just as slow as can be
But lately he's been searching for a high that's fancy and free
Crawlin' on his journey, through the wide open trail
Leaving behind a silver trace, as this snail sets sail

[chorus]
Oh, Mr. Snail, you're spiraling down a winding road
Chasing the dragonfly, tryin' to lighten your load
Through the cornfields you wander, leaving a snail slime trail
But you gotta break free, Mr. Snail, before your soul turns pale
